14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 330.99 of Title 63, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. Oklahoma Task Force 1 (OK-TF1) shall be recognized as the
19 official deployment asset team for urban search and rescue missions
20 and for floods and disasters in the State of Oklahoma; provided,
21 however, OK-TF1 shall not be deployed for wildland firefighting.
22 OK-TF1 shall be the first deployed asset for any Emergency
23 Management Assistance Compact-related requests outside of the State
24 of Oklahoma during any declared disasters.
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3831 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 B. The Oklahoma Department of Emergency Management is
2 authorized to promulgate and enforce rules governing the
3 administration, allowable uses, and oversight of the Oklahoma Task
4 Force 1 Revolving Fund.
5 C. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
6 fund for the Oklahoma Department of Emergency Management, to be
7 designated the "Oklahoma Task Force 1 Revolving Fund". The fund
8 shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations,
9 and shall consist of all monies deposited to the credit of the fund
10 by law. All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
11 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Department of
12 Emergency Management for the direct reimbursement of participating
13 agencies of Oklahoma Task Force 1. Expenditures from the fund shall
14 be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims
15 filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of
16 Management and Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
17 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
18 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
19 There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Department of
20 Emergency Management, from any monies not otherwise appropriated
21 from the General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal
22 year ending June 30, 2027, the sum of _____________________
23 ($___________) to be deposited in the Oklahoma Task Force 1
24 Revolving Fund, and used by participating agencies of Oklahoma Task
