3 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
4 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
5 There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Department of
6 Emergency Management, from any monies not otherwise appropriated
7 from the General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal
8 year ending June 30, 2027, the sum of _____________________
9 ($___________) to be deposited in the Oklahoma Task Force 1
10 Revolving Fund. Of those funds appropriated, the sum of
11 _____________________ ($___________) shall be dedicated and utilized
12 by the Oklahoma City team of Oklahoma Task Force 1 solely for
13 personnel, equipment, logistics, transportation, lodging, and
14 operational expenses. Funds appropriated may also be used for
15 deployment readiness and capability enhancements including training,
16 specialized equipment, communications systems, canine acquisition,
17 care and training, and other resources necessary to support disaster
18 response deployments. Appropriated funds shall not be used for
19 routine or daily fire department operations, staffing, facilities,
20 maintenance, or other expenses not related to the task force. Of
21 those funds appropriated, the sum of _____________________
22 ($___________) shall be dedicated and utilized by the Tulsa team of
23 Oklahoma Task Force 1 solely for personnel, equipment, logistics,
24 transportation, lodging, and operational expenses. Funds
